    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"648495\">Christian Merten</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/.60Set.2Eencard_iUnion.60/near/511087596\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Yes, and it's in <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/23849\">#23849</a> (not the <code>card</code> lemmas though, because <code>Pairwise</code> only takes <code>Type*</code>).</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I’ve run into this constraint before, as well. Is there a reason <code>Pairwise</code> can’t generalize?</p>",
